#. HTML: <section class="sutta" id="sn10.12"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "sn10.12:0.1"
msgid "Saṃyutta Nikāya 10 "
msgstr "Linked Discourses 10 "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn10.12:0.2"
msgid "1. Indakavagga "
msgstr "1. With Indaka "

#. HTML: </p><h1>
msgctxt "sn10.12:0.3"
msgid "12. Āḷavakasutta "
msgstr "12. With Āḷavaka "

#. HTML: </h1></div><p><span class="evam">
#. REF: pts1ed1.214, pts2ed1.461, sc1
msgctxt "sn10.12:1.1"
msgid "Evaṃ me sutaṃ—"
msgstr "So I have heard. "

#. HTML: </span>
msgctxt "sn10.12:1.2"
msgid "ekaṃ samayaṃ bhagavā āḷaviyaṃ viharati āḷavakassa yakkhassa bhavane. "
msgstr "At one time the Buddha was staying near Āḷavī in the haunt of the native spirit Āḷavaka. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn10.12:1.3"
msgid "Atha kho āḷavako yakkho yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā bhagavantaṃ etadavoca: "
msgstr "Then the native spirit Āḷavaka went up to the Buddha, and said to him: "

msgctxt "sn10.12:1.4"
msgid "“nikkhama, samaṇā”ti. "
msgstr "“Get out, ascetic!” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn10.12:1.5"
msgid "“Sādhāvuso”ti bhagavā nikkhami. "
msgstr "Saying, “All right, sir,” the Buddha went out. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn10.12:1.6"
msgid "“Pavisa, samaṇā”ti. "
msgstr "“Get in, ascetic!” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn10.12:1.7"
msgid "“Sādhāvuso”ti bhagavā pāvisi. "
msgstr "Saying, “All right, sir,” the Buddha went in. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn10.12:1.8"
msgid "Dutiyampi kho āḷavako yakkho bhagavantaṃ etadavoca: "
msgstr "And for a second time the native spirit Āḷavaka said to the Buddha, "

msgctxt "sn10.12:1.9"
msgid "“nikkhama, samaṇā”ti. "
msgstr "“Get out, ascetic!” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn10.12:1.10"
msgid "“Sādhāvuso”ti bhagavā nikkhami. "
msgstr "Saying, “All right, sir,” the Buddha went out. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn10.12:1.11"
msgid "“Pavisa, samaṇā”ti. "
msgstr "“Get in, ascetic!” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn10.12:1.12"
msgid "“Sādhāvuso”ti bhagavā pāvisi. "
msgstr "Saying, “All right, sir,” the Buddha went in. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn10.12:1.13"
msgid "Tatiyampi kho āḷavako yakkho bhagavantaṃ etadavoca: "
msgstr "And for a third time the native spirit Āḷavaka said to the Buddha, "

msgctxt "sn10.12:1.14"
msgid "“nikkhama, samaṇā”ti. "
msgstr "“Get out, ascetic!” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn10.12:1.15"
msgid "“Sādhāvuso”ti bhagavā nikkhami. "
msgstr "Saying, “All right, sir,” the Buddha went out. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn10.12:1.16"
msgid "“Pavisa, samaṇā”ti. "
msgstr "“Get in, ascetic!” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn10.12:1.17"
msgid "“Sādhāvuso”ti bhagavā pāvisi. "
msgstr "Saying, “All right, sir,” the Buddha went in. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn10.12:1.18"
msgid "Catutthampi kho āḷavako yakkho bhagavantaṃ etadavoca: "
msgstr "And for a fourth time the native spirit Āḷavaka said to the Buddha, "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn10.12:1.19"
msgid "“nikkhama, samaṇā”ti. "
msgstr "“Get out, ascetic!” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn10.12:1.20"
msgid "“Na khvāhaṃ taṃ, āvuso, nikkhamissāmi. "
msgstr "“No, sir, I won’t get out. "

msgctxt "sn10.12:1.21"
msgid "Yaṃ te karaṇīyaṃ taṃ karohī”ti. "
msgstr "Do whatever you have to do.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn10.12:1.22"
msgid "“Pañhaṃ taṃ, samaṇa, pucchissāmi. "
msgstr "“I will ask you a question, ascetic. "

msgctxt "sn10.12:1.23"
msgid "Sace me na byākarissasi, cittaṃ vā te khipissāmi, hadayaṃ vā te phālessāmi, pādesu vā gahetvā pāragaṅgāya khipissāmī”ti. "
msgstr "If you don’t answer me, I’ll drive you insane, or explode your heart, or grab you by the feet and throw you to the far shore of the Ganges!” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn10.12:1.24"
msgid "“Na khvāhaṃ taṃ, āvuso, passāmi sadevake loke samārake sabrahmake sassamaṇabrāhmaṇiyā pajāya sadevamanussāya, yo me cittaṃ vā khipeyya hadayaṃ vā phāleyya, pādesu vā gahetvā pāragaṅgāya khipeyya. "
msgstr "“I don’t see anyone in this world with its gods, Māras, and Brahmās, this population with its ascetics and brahmins, its gods and humans who could do that to me. "

#. VAR: () → (atha kho āḷavako yakkho bhagavantaṃ gāthāya ajjhabhāsi.) (bj, pts2)
msgctxt "sn10.12:1.25"
msgid "Api ca tvaṃ, āvuso, puccha yadā kaṅkhasī”ti (). "
msgstr "But anyway, ask what you wish.” "

#. HTML: </p><blockquote class="gatha"><p>
#. REF: pts2ed1.462, sc2, verse-num-sc846
msgctxt "sn10.12:2.1"
msgid "“Kiṃsūdha vittaṃ purisassa seṭṭhaṃ, "
msgstr "“What’s a person’s best wealth? "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn10.12:2.2"
msgid "Kiṃsu suciṇṇaṃ sukhamāvahāti; "
msgstr "What brings happiness when practiced well? "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn10.12:2.3"
msgid "Kiṃsu have sādutaraṃ rasānaṃ, "
msgstr "What’s the sweetest taste of all? "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn10.12:2.4"
msgid "Kathaṃjīviṃ jīvitamāhu seṭṭhan”ti. "
msgstr "The one who they say has the best life: how do they live?” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc3, verse-num-sc847
msgctxt "sn10.12:3.1"
msgid "“Saddhīdha vittaṃ purisassa seṭṭhaṃ, "
msgstr "“Faith here is a person’s best wealth. "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn10.12:3.2"
msgid "Dhammo suciṇṇo sukhamāvahāti; "
msgstr "The teaching brings happiness when practiced well. "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn10.12:3.3"
msgid "Saccaṃ have sādutaraṃ rasānaṃ, "
msgstr "Truth is the sweetest taste of all. "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn10.12:3.4"
msgid "Paññājīviṃ jīvitamāhu seṭṭhan”ti. "
msgstr "The one who they say has the best life lives by wisdom.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc4, verse-num-sc848
msgctxt "sn10.12:4.1"
msgid "“Kathaṃsu tarati oghaṃ, "
msgstr "“How do you cross the flood? "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn10.12:4.2"
msgid "kathaṃsu tarati aṇṇavaṃ; "
msgstr "How do you cross the deluge? "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn10.12:4.3"
msgid "Kathaṃsu dukkhamacceti, "
msgstr "How do you get over suffering? "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn10.12:4.4"
msgid "kathaṃsu parisujjhatī”ti. "
msgstr "How do you get purified?” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc5, verse-num-sc849
msgctxt "sn10.12:5.1"
msgid "“Saddhāya tarati oghaṃ, "
msgstr "“By faith you cross the flood, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn10.12:5.2"
msgid "appamādena aṇṇavaṃ; "
msgstr "and by diligence the deluge. "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn10.12:5.3"
msgid "Vīriyena dukkhamacceti, "
msgstr "By energy you get past suffering, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn10.12:5.4"
msgid "paññāya parisujjhatī”ti. "
msgstr "and you’re purified by wisdom.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts2ed1.463, sc6, verse-num-sc850
msgctxt "sn10.12:6.1"
msgid "“Kathaṃsu labhate paññaṃ, "
msgstr "“How do you get wisdom? "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn10.12:6.2"
msgid "kathaṃsu vindate dhanaṃ; "
msgstr "How do you earn wealth? "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn10.12:6.3"
msgid "Kathaṃsu kittiṃ pappoti, "
msgstr "How do you get a good reputation? "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn10.12:6.4"
msgid "kathaṃ mittāni ganthati; "
msgstr "How do you hold on to friends? "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn10.12:6.5"
msgid "Asmā lokā paraṃ lokaṃ, "
msgstr "How do the departed not grieve "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn10.12:6.6"
msgid "kathaṃ pecca na socatī”ti. "
msgstr "when passing from this world to the next?” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc7, verse-num-sc851
msgctxt "sn10.12:7.1"
msgid "“Saddahāno arahataṃ, "
msgstr "“One who is diligent and discerning "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn10.12:7.2"
msgid "dhammaṃ nibbānapattiyā; "
msgstr "gains wisdom by wanting to learn, "

#. HTML: <br>
#. VAR: Sussūsaṃ → sussūsā (bj, pts1-2)
msgctxt "sn10.12:7.3"
msgid "Sussūsaṃ labhate paññaṃ, "
msgstr "having faith in the perfected ones, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn10.12:7.4"
msgid "appamatto vicakkhaṇo. "
msgstr "and the teaching for becoming extinguished. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts1ed1.215, sc8, verse-num-sc852
msgctxt "sn10.12:8.1"
msgid "Patirūpakārī dhuravā, "
msgstr "Being responsible, acting appropriately, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn10.12:8.2"
msgid "uṭṭhātā vindate dhanaṃ; "
msgstr "and working hard you earn wealth. "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn10.12:8.3"
msgid "Saccena kittiṃ pappoti, "
msgstr "Truthfulness wins you a good reputation. "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn10.12:8.4"
msgid "dadaṃ mittāni ganthati; "
msgstr "You hold on to friends by giving. "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn10.12:8.5"
msgid "Asmā lokā paraṃ lokaṃ, "
msgstr "That’s how the departed do not grieve "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn10.12:8.6"
msgid "evaṃ pecca na socati. "
msgstr "when passing from this world to the next. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc9, verse-num-sc853
msgctxt "sn10.12:9.1"
msgid "Yassete caturo dhammā, "
msgstr "A faithful householder "

# NOTE: BB’s “seeker of the household life” is wrong and he corrected it in AN to"householder, i.e. following Cone this = Skt gṛhamedhin.
#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn10.12:9.2"
msgid "saddhassa gharamesino; "
msgstr "who has these four qualities "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn10.12:9.3"
msgid "Saccaṃ dhammo dhiti cāgo, "
msgstr "does not grieve after passing away: "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn10.12:9.4"
msgid "sa ve pecca na socati. "
msgstr "truth, principle, steadfastness, and generosity. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts2ed1.464, sc10, verse-num-sc854
msgctxt "sn10.12:10.1"
msgid "Iṅgha aññepi pucchassu, "
msgstr "Go ahead, ask others as well, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn10.12:10.2"
msgid "puthū samaṇabrāhmaṇe; "
msgstr "there are many ascetics and brahmins. "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn10.12:10.3"
msgid "Yadi saccā dhammā cāgā, "
msgstr "See whether anything better is found "

# NOTE: See BB for readings. the Chinese at SA2 325 and SA 1326 support dama or danta here.
#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn10.12:10.4"
msgid "khantyā bhiyyodha vijjatī”ti. "
msgstr "than truth, self-control, generosity, and patience.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc11, verse-num-sc855
msgctxt "sn10.12:11.1"
msgid "“Kathaṃ nu dāni puccheyyaṃ, "
msgstr "“Why now would I question "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn10.12:11.2"
msgid "puthū samaṇabrāhmaṇe; "
msgstr "the many ascetics and brahmins? "

#. HTML: <br>
#. VAR: Yohaṃ → sohaṃ (bj, pts2) | svāhaṃ (mr)
msgctxt "sn10.12:11.3"
msgid "Yohaṃ ajja pajānāmi, "
msgstr "Today I understand "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn10.12:11.4"
msgid "yo attho samparāyiko. "
msgstr "what’s good for the next life. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc12, verse-num-sc856
msgctxt "sn10.12:12.1"
msgid "Atthāya vata me buddho, "
msgstr "It was truly for my benefit "

#. HTML: <br>
#. VAR: vāsāyāḷavimāgamā → … māgato (pts1, mr)
msgctxt "sn10.12:12.2"
msgid "vāsāyāḷavimāgamā; "
msgstr "that the Buddha came to stay at Āḷavī. "

#. HTML: <br>
#. VAR: Yohaṃ → sohaṃ (bj, pts2)
msgctxt "sn10.12:12.3"
msgid "Yohaṃ ajja pajānāmi, "
msgstr "Today I understand "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn10.12:12.4"
msgid "yattha dinnaṃ mahapphalaṃ. "
msgstr "where a gift is very fruitful. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc13, verse-num-sc857
msgctxt "sn10.12:13.1"
msgid "So ahaṃ vicarissāmi, "
msgstr "I myself will journey "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn10.12:13.2"
msgid "Gāmā gāmaṃ purā puraṃ; "
msgstr "village to village, town to town, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn10.12:13.3"
msgid "Namassamāno sambuddhaṃ, "
msgstr "paying homage to the Buddha, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn10.12:13.4"
msgid "Dhammassa ca sudhammatan”ti. "
msgstr "and the natural excellence of the teaching!” "

#. HTML: </p></blockquote><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "sn10.12:13.5"
msgid "Indakavaggo paṭhamo. "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: </p><blockquote class="uddanagatha"><p>
#. REF: pts2ed1.465, sc14
msgctxt "sn10.12:14.1"
msgid "Indako sakka sūci ca, "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn10.12:14.2"
msgid "Maṇibhaddo ca sānu ca; "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn10.12:14.3"
msgid "Piyaṅkara punabbasu sudatto ca, "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn10.12:14.4"
msgid "Dve sukkā cīraāḷavīti dvādasa. "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: </p></blockquote><p class="endsutta">
msgctxt "sn10.12:14.5"
msgid "Yakkhasaṃyuttaṃ samattaṃ. "
msgstr "The Linked Discourses with Native Spirits are complete."

#. HTML: </p></article></section></body></html>
